deck: An American illustrator known for merchandising artwork, homage pieces, and variant covers.
description:
Timothy Lim is a freelance artist and illustrator who began his career with fan art publications, beginning with back page art for G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero issue 24. Following publications in Udon's Street Fighter Tribute #1 and Mega Man Tribute #1, he was hired as a freelance illustrator for Mighty Fine / We Love Fine, producing licensed artwork for merchandise including shirts, posters, prints, and bags. His clientele includes licensed work for Marvel®, Lucasfilm®, Hasbro®, Valve®, Axe Cop®, and much more. His work has appeared in the documentary "Dear Mr. Watterson" and he has been hired to do work for Stan Lee, Dan Gilvezan, and Claudia Wells. Artwork by Lim has been used for official merchandise for San Diego Comic-Con 2015, Emerald City Comicon, C2E2, and Alamo City Comic Con.

Lim's recent comic book work includes a tribute work to Harold Ramis in Ghostbusters #17 - Mass Hysteria! part 5. As of 2015, he has begun freelance cover work in collaboration with Heroes & Fantasies: this includes variant covers for Back To the Future #1 - Untold Tales and Alternate Timelines, James Bond #1 - VARGR, and A&A: The Adventures of Archer & Armstrong #1. His wraparound cover for Street Fighter x G.I. Joe #1 became the rarest cover printed for that run after the supply truck carrying 1,000 copies was struck by another vehicle, destroying most of the copies and leaving less than 200 intact.
name: Timothy Lim
